  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "To reduce the bandwidth and CPU requirements for beacon nodes in a large staking service, we should be able to delegate which beacon node to use for specific attestation subnets. Subscription requests, creating aggregates and publishing attestations should be directed to the beacon node assigned to that attestation/aggregate‚Äôs subnet.\n\nThis is a continuation of the [Sentry Beacon Nodes](https://docs.teku.consensys.io/how-to/use-sentry-nodes#configure-sentry-nodes)\n\nThe BN subnet subscriptions could be spread across different BNs based on the sentry node configuration file. \nExample:\n```\n{\n    \"beacon_nodes\": [\n        {\n            \"attestation_subnets\": {\n                \"start\": 0,\n                \"count\": 32,\n                \"endpoints\": [\"http://nodeA:9051\"]\n            },\n            \"attestation_subnets\": {\n                \"start\": 33,\n                \"count\": 31,\n                \"endpoints\": [\"http://nodeB:9051\"]\n            },\n            \"sync_committee_subnets\": {\n                \"start\": 0,\n                \"count\": 32\n                \"endpoints\": [\"http://nodeA:9051\"]\n            }\n            \"sync_committee_subnets\": {\n                \"start\": 33,\n                \"count\": 31\n                \"endpoints\": [\"http://nodeB:9051\"]\n            }\n        }\n    ]\n}\n```",
