    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "IMO since the subnet [subscription revamp](https://github.com/Consensys/teku/issues/7296) has been merged, this issue could be closed.\n- The motivation behind it was to reduce cpu requirements for BNs because they were subscribing to all subnets but they are now subscribing to 2 persistent subnets only ans we already measured a nice cpu usage drop since the change has been merged\n- This adds  a lot complexity to the sentry nodes configuration and make it error prone and hard to stay consistent\n- We didn't get clear feedback about the sentry nodes feature and not sure if building such feature on top of it could be useful from an end user point of view",
